Hey KERNEL Fam,
Since leaving the KERNEL we have directed efforts to community building in our SLACK and are now preparing to hold our first community event.  The event is led by community members and will feature five founders hosting topics/pitches/demos at their own tables (all trial and error at this stage). We will be holding these events monthly should you ever want to join us.:seedling:All are always welcome and happy to introduce you to our growing family of Rare Ones:-) Also open to collabs/co-meets and the like with other growing communities in the KERNEL.

I have decided to drop out of the presentation to investors / mentors today. I can‚Äôt visualise the whole picture for Thrivy atm, the gas prices would kill the whole business model

<https://thrivy.substack.com/p/putting-thrivy-on-hold>
ALEX was meant to be traded on Thrivy. Every retail person would be able to happily acquire ALEX!
The mentors offer really great guidance and have a lot of experience. If you present the challenges you're facing, they may be able to help you find a workaround! :fire:
can I still present even if I have dropped out of the presentation?
I don‚Äôt see why not! I mean, you just need a table on Airmeet right? ü•∞

Yes <@U016M08G1M4>  you should present! - you can explain these issues

Also would Matic‚Äôs plasma based second layer help? <@U0172CM3049> is the woman to talk to

I had a burn out after my pt website... perhaps

First, I need to answer questions about costs. (I) how much is a person expected to accumulate in x days. (ii) how much they need to meaningfully benefit from DeFi (iii) how would thrivy survive in the first couple of months. It‚Äôs a business, so need revenue too

I have a feeling that the numbers are prohibitively exorbitant. I have like 1k DAI that I‚Äôm not investing because it is too expensive. How can a person with ¬£0.5 invest then. Someone suggested using xDAI. Perhaps it is a way. I don‚Äôt know enough about it. I think DSR gets locked up and that mints xDAI and then chai is the interest bearing part in the bridge. Although mechanics of interest earning are unclear.

Perhaps what UNI does is a better first step. I was thinking about doing it that way too. Perhaps, we could embed UNI / portions of their codebase into Thrivy? <@U016Z7XQC7N>  <@U016QSTSQQM>
I would say differentiate from UNI but checkin w Ayra as he is super knowledgeable
